hands_on_practices.problem:
A simplified population model for a particular insect species is described by a linear recurrence relation. Let $y_n$ denote the population size in year $n$. The model posits that the population in any given year is determined by the populations of the two preceding years according to the second-order homogeneous linear difference equation:
$$y_{n+2} = y_{n+1} + 6y_n$$
To analyze the dynamics of this population, this second-order equation can be converted into a first-order two-dimensional system. We define a state vector $\mathbf{x}_n$
$$ \mathbf{x}_n = \begin{pmatrix} y_{n+1} \\ y_n \end{pmatrix} $$
The evolution of this state vector is then described by a matrix equation $\mathbf{x}_{n+1} = M \mathbf{x}_n$, where $M$ is a constant 2x2 matrix called the transition matrix.

What are the eigenvalues of the transition matrix $M$?

A. {3, -2}

B. {2, -3}

C. {1, 6}

D. {-1, -6}

E. {2, 3}
